The purity of the synthesized Pt-Pd/NiO-NPs/SWCNTs nanocomposite was characterized using the EDS method (Fig. 1
                        ). The results showed the presence of Pt, Pd, C, Ni, and O elements. The data confirmed the purity of the synthesized Pt-Pd/NiO-NPs/SWCNT nanocomposite. The TEM results, shown in Fig. 2
                        A, confirmed the presence of single-wall carbon nanotubes decorated by spherical nanoparticles (Pt-Pd/NiO-NPs), which is in line with our predictions. The XRD patterns of the Pt-Pd/NiO-NPs/SWCNTs are shown in Fig. 2B. The results revealed six planes with miller indexes [111], [200], [220], [311], and [222] relative to NiO nanoparticles (JCPDS No. 001-1239) and [002] relative to the single-wall carbon nanotube. Because of the presence of Pt and Pd in the NiO nanoparticle structure and the low concentration of these nanoparticles, clear planes relative to these particles could not be detected.

The Tafel plot relative to the electro-oxidation of 350 μM nalbuphine with a scan rate of 50 mV/s was recorded at the surface of the Pt-Pd/NiO-NPs/SWCNTs/EMICH3SO3
                        −/CPE. Using the slope of the Tafel plot in the presence of nalbuphine, the value of the electron transfer coefficient (α) was calculated as 0.64 (Fig. 6
                        ).
